The paper discusses a framework for learning effective questioning strategies for knowledge acquisition through an interactive game. This involves deep reinforcement learning and generalized matrix factorization, which are commonly used in the fields of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also deals with natural language processing and user interaction, which fall under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper focuses on human-computer interaction and user experience, which are relevant to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
